      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The straight-line depreciation formula is (Cost - Salvage Value) / Useful Life. For your machine, that's (50,000 - 5,000) / 5, which equals 9,000 per year. You can imagine the machine's value dropping by exactly 9,000 each year, just like a bank account with a steady, predictable withdrawal. This method assumes the asset wears out evenly over time, which is a common assumption for things like office furniture or machinery. Good luck with your exam!",
